p: As depicted in the same table, the alkaline phosphates (ALP), alanine aminotransferase (ALT) and aspartate aminotransferase (AST) activities in all experimental groups were relatively similar and in the normal range. These data of liver functions could be important in the diagnosis of diseases as well as in the investigation and thorough assessment of feed, drugs and extracts used in feeding trials. They suggest that the insect-containing diets do not negatively affect the liver function of the quails.
